{{Quote|First proposed by Can Lar, a Gathi working for CoMar Weapons, the v-150 planet defender was initially rejected by CoMar as 'militarily useless and an engineering impossibility.'|A compilation of Galactic Empire documents by Major Arhul Hextrophon|<ref name="ISB2">[[Imperial Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''Imperial Sourcebook'', Second Edition]]</ref>}}
The '''Gathi''' was a group of which [[Can Lar]] was a member. At one point he worked for the [[CoMar Combat Systems/Legends|CoMar Combat Systems]] company, where he proposed a design for an anti-[[Orbit/Legends|orbital]] [[Ion cannon/Legends|ion cannon]]. After the company rejected the proposal, Lar quit working there and instead presented the design to [[Kuat Drive Yards/Legends|Kuat Drive Yards]], which went on to realize it as the [[V-150 Planet Defender/Legends|v-150 Planet Defender]]. Shortly after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Lar being a Gathi was mentioned in a compilation of [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] documents made by [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Historian/Legends|historian]] [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Arhul Hextrophon/Legends|Arhul Hextrophon]] for Alliance [[Supreme Commander (Alliance)/Legends|Supreme Commander]] [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] and other Rebel [[Officer/Legends|officers]].<ref name="ISB2" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Gathi were first mentioned in the [[1989]] ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]'', written by [[Greg Gorden]] and published by [[West End Games]] for use with ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="ISB">''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]''</ref>

